<span id="freeTextContainer4742842372122387179"><b>Reread on 2017.02.08 in my native language.</b><br/><br/>I... Just... Can&apos;t...<br/><br/> <img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1437883414ra/15641251.gif' width='400' height='200' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/> <br/><br/>Even if I had the biggest support team ever (thank youuu!), I couldn&apos;t force myself to read any further than fifty pages. <br/><br/>At least now I can put a finger on a thing I don&apos;t like - it&apos;s the style. I guess I just like epic fantasy with the normal amount of description, not a crazy pace and writing - while reading &quot;The Black Company&quot; I found nothing to &quot;hold on&quot; - characters are scattered, the environment changes abruptly, to feel &quot;i</span>
  <span id="freeText4742842372122387179" style="display:none"><b>Reread on 2017.02.08 in my native language.</b><br><br>I... Just... Can't...<br><br> <img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1437883414ra/15641251.gif" width="400" height="200" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"> <br><br>Even if I had the biggest support team ever (thank youuu!), I couldn't force myself to read any further than fifty pages. <br><br>At least now I can put a finger on a thing I don't like - it's the style. I guess I just like epic fantasy with the normal amount of description, not a crazy pace and writing - while reading "The Black Company" I found nothing to "hold on" - characters are scattered, the environment changes abruptly, to feel "included" you need to try very, very hard. And still, what I made of the first thirty pages was that they were just leaving the city. <br><br>I am also putting it into my "no-just-no" shelve - I hope it will prevent me from reading it for the third time. <br><br><b>Original review.</b><br><br>Wait...? What? Emmm... Ahhhh... Yes, so... Wait, wait... There... Who? Trousers? Ehhhummm... <br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1469726195ra/19851464.gif" width="400" height="č00" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>I so don't get it. I don't know if this is the e.version of the book that is so completely terrible that I am just unable to understand what is happening, or my English is just having a day off with a Queen Of English language, or it's just completely and utterly boring? It's messy, tangled, simply unreadable. There seem to be new characters growing in the middle of the sentence, they are gone so fast, that it leaves you puzzled after each paragraph. Some mystical creature is hanging around - but why they are chasing it? What is it? WHAAAAT??? No, no way I am going to understand it. I tried. Really hard, but that's all I got from the story. <br><br>It says that G.Cook shaped fantasy in a new way. BUT I JUST DON'T GET IT.</span>
